entries.femaleVariant: Sit. I have not eaten since yesterday.
[Sit]
Give me the best on the menu.
Can't believe I'm sayin' this, but this 'Saka scum might actually prove useful.
He's a well-trained dog – needs orders, that's all.
And when he outlives his purpose, we'll flatline him.
Anything that isn't local, please.
You don't know this city. Lemme help.
OK, you handle that.
You're a stranger in a strange land. Goin' with you.
Yeah, got enough on my plate as it is. I'll let you handle that.
entries.maleVariant: Got enough on my plate as it is. I'll let you handle that.

entries.femaleVariant: So I shall.
Now, we part.
Reconnaissance is required.
What're you doin'? Don't let him off his leash!
Cook! Louder, louder!
Yorinobu...
OK. I have laid the plan.
One. We break into Arasaka Industrial Park. One and a half – we hack Hanako-sama's float.
Three. I get onto the float.
Four. I convince Hanako-sama of the truth.
Done dumber shit than this before, so...
Five – Oda zeroes us.
Well, sounds like a suicide run, but done dumber shit than this so...
Forgot five – Oda zeroes us and pisses on our corpses.
Two. During the parade, with my help, you eliminate any snipers.
He won't ever be less than a foot away from Hanako.
We'll see about that.
Takemura's not a bad guy.
Bridge we might cross, but only might. We'll see.
Chill, Johnny.
Glad we're on the same page.
Could still be dangerous.
He's not on his A-game, sure. But even without implants he could decomish us easily.
Not a bad guy?! He was Saburo fucking Arasaka's bodyguard!
Think his pretty eyes landed him that gig?
Where's that come from? Ever seen him in action?
Nah. Just know... from the way he walks, the look in his eye…
entries.maleVariant: Nah. Just know... from the way he walks, look in his eye...

entries.femaleVariant: We'll come back to this later.
Let him stray even a couple of feet 'n' you can say goodbye to his fuckin' honor!
He's "'Saka scum" to you, I know that, but Goro's not a bad guy.
Oda would not dare raise his hand against me.
Hmm, true. And you with your hands, skills, mind of a thief…
In the flesh.
Surrendered it to him.
He eliminated the last obstacle between himself and complete power.
And they...
Go with him, V.
You never know what a dog's thinkin'. Might be the same thing.
I highly recommend the yakitori today.
See you tomorrow.
I hope you enjoyed it. Please come again.
Really out to get us killed, aren't you.
What about me?
That is a different matter. I would advise you to watch your distance.
This your elaborate seppuku ritual?
What? Why?
Far as I can see, you're tryna get us killed. Really like to know why.
The risks are substantial, yes. But we have no choice. Hanako-sama is our only chance.
You have nothing to lose, as I do. I see it in your eyes.
Things even more stupid than stealing from Arasaka?
None dumber yet, no. Set the bar pretty high with that one...
Will you just stand there?
You may not be hungry, but I am. Please, sit.
Wh-wh-why'd Saburo tolerate it all? Can't get my head around it. Coulda kept his son on a short leash.
entries.maleVariant: Why'd Saburo tolerate it all? Can't get my head around it. Coulda kept his son on a short leash.

entries.femaleVariant: Arasaka-sama was a strong and disciplined man. The strongest man I have ever known.
And yet, at a critical moment, he showed a weakness.
For Yorinobu.
For his daughter.
When Yorinobu formed his band of hounds, declared war on his own family, Arasaka-sama could have crushed him with one word.
Yet he did not. For he did not wish his daughter to suffer.
When Yorinobu returned, his tail between his legs, she persuaded her father to give him a second chance.
Do you understand? Hanako-sama saved Yorinobu from the consequences of his deeds.
Might have a change of heart now.
You blame Hanako for this, too.
Wait... think she's complicit in Saburo's murder?
entries.maleVariant: Wait... ya think she's complicit in Saburo's murder?

entries.femaleVariant: I think we are all to blame. We allowed ourselves to be tricked.
Where's Yorinobu's rebellious streak come from?
No one knows this.
Perhaps soon I shall ask him. In person.
Why'd Saburo allow it to happen?
Yorinobu – where'd he get his rebellious streak?
What are the factions?
Old man's death couldn't have helped.
Old man's death must've really fed the flames between the different factions.
What's the balance of power look like now?
entries.maleVariant: An' what's the balance of power look like now?

entries.femaleVariant: Kiji longs for stability, the old order. They are united behind Hanako-sama.
The liberal wing, Hato, support Michiko-sama – Saburo's granddaughter. I know little about her.
And then there is Taka, treacherous dogs who support Yorinobu.
Not to mention even smaller factions, which--
Tell me about 'em some other time.
Feels like that's about to change. Long as we get Hanako to believe our version of events...
Got factions inside Arasaka? What are they?
There are three – Kiji, Hato and Taka.
What is this?!
Heh, Yakitori.
Arasaka... An empire built to last.
Before Yorinobu set fire to it from the inside.
<mothertongue l="jpn" m="kuso" b="All of this began with him – the factions, power struggles... All of this... " a="…"/>
But we will correct this soon.
We must reach her first.
Conscience could also come into play. Assuming she's got one.
Time for some reconnaissance. Wait for my call.
That is exactly what happened.
Sawdust and plastic.
[Eat]
Will you join me?
Might as well.
Not this time.
Sure, why not.
Get there on my own, thanks.
Very well. I will soon leave as well. See you there.
Let us go from here.
Agreed. This we will do together.
[Stand and start recon]
[Stand]
Sure.
No, thanks.
And?
System's ours.
Done. System's ours.
The shard works. Good – the easy work we have done.
To break into Arasaka Industrial Park will not be such a "bed of roses." But before we discuss that…
I'm a thief, ain't I?
Two-bit thief, ain't I? Keep sayin' so yourself.
Not without reason.
[Eat]
